Blocks.childText: 154 MY FAITH LOOKS UP TO THEE. 6s & 4s. Spiritual Songs. 1. My faith looks up to thee, Thou Lamb of Cal - va - ry ; Sa- vior di-vine Now hear me gbb 9:52 0-22 while I pray Take all my guilt away o, let me from this day Be whol-ly thine. 386. 387. Christ, our Confidence. Worthy the Lamb. 1 MY faith looks up to thee, 1 "GLORY to God on high Thou Lamb of Calvary ; Let heaven and earth reply, Savior divine! "Praise ye his name 199 Now hear me while I pray; His love and grace adore, Take all my guilt away Who all our sorrows bore Oh let me from this day Sing aloud evermore- Be wholly thine. "Worthy the Lamb." 2 May thy rich grace impart 2 Ye who surround the throne, Strength to my fainting heart, Cheerfully join in one, My zeal inspire ; Praising his name: As thou hast died for me, His love and grace adore, Oh ! may my love to thee, Who all our sorrows bore Pure, warm, and changeless be, Sing aloud evermore A living fire. "Worthy the Lamb." 3 While life's dark maze I tread, 3 Join all ye ransomed race And griefs around me spread, Our Lord and God to bless Be thou my guide; Praise ye his name: Bid darkness turn to day, On him we fix our choice, Wipe sorrow's tears away, In him we will rejoice, Nor let me ever stray Shouting with heart and voice- From thee aside. 66 Worthy the Lamb." 4 When ends life's transient dream, 4 Soon must we close our race, When death's cold sullen stream Yet will we never cease Shall o'er me roll; Praising his name: Blest Savior, then in love, But as we upward wing, Fear and distrust remove: Hail him our gracious King, Oh bear me safe above- And through the heavens sing- A ransomed soul. "Worthy the Lamb."
